gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 136, Kings 110
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers defeated the Kings, 136-110. Donovan Mitchell recorded a game-high 29 points, along with five assists and five 3PM for the Cavaliers, while Evan Mobley added 11 points, 14 rebounds and seven assists in the victory. Domantas Sabonis tallied 12 points, 19 rebounds and 15 assists for the Kings in the losing effort, his 15th triple-double of the season and 47th of his career. The Cavaliers win their sixth straight game as they improve to 32-16 on the season, while the Kings fall to 29-20.
